args-inject: How it differs from other known libraries

* Commandline-handling libraries

   At the time of writing, following are known to me:

   * {{{http://commons.apache.org/cli/}commons-cli}} by Apache Commons Project

   * {{{https://args4j.dev.java.net}args4j}} by Kohsuke Kawaguchi

   []

   Plus, some inspiration comes from cvs, svn, svnkit, spring and other projects.

* Important differences

   * unmarshalling, i.e. translating the value to the target type <<<(note: args4j has unmarshalling)>>>

   * support for declarative setup <<<(note: args4j has declarative setup)>>>

   * injection to client (subcommand) object

   * explicit, straightforward support for subcommands

   * exception handling

